space.arim.api.platform

Interface PlatformTabCompletion<T,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the platform specific command sender object
    R - the type of the platform specific player object
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPlatformCommands, BungeeCommands, SpigotCommands, SpongeCommands

    public interface PlatformTabCompletion<T,R>
    Adds simple tab completions. Matches given command arguments against streams of Strings, players, or command senders.
    The last argument is used for matching and all others are ignored. If the argument array is empty or null, an empty string is used, meaning the result will be the elements of the source stream.

    There is no guarantee that returned lists are mutable. Thus, sorting any returned lists with List.sort(Comparator) may or may not work; it is unsupported. Therefore it is recommended to explicitly use the methods designed for sorting. Each method returning an unsorted list has a sorted variant with an optionally specified Comparator
    Author:
    A248

      • getPlayerNamesTabComplete

        List<String> getPlayerNamesTabComplete(Stream<? extends R> players,
                                       String[] args)
        Gets tab completions based on player names matching the command arguments.

        The returned list is unsorted by default.
        For sorting, use:
        * getPlayerNamesTabCompleteSorted(Stream, String[]) for natural ordering
        * getPlayerNamesTabCompleteSorted(Stream, String[], Comparator) to specify a Comparator
        Parameters:
        players - a stream of players
        args - the command arguments
        Returns:
        an unsorted list of matching names

      • getCommandSendersTabComplete

        List<String> getCommandSendersTabComplete(Stream<T> senders,
                                          String consoleRepresentation,
                                          String[] args)
        Gets tab completions based on command senders matching the command argument.
        This is similar to getPlayerNamesTabComplete(Stream, String[]), however, it includes the console as a possible choice. The representation of the console as a string is passed as a parameter.
        When matching against the stream of command senders, each command sender is evaluated to a String; if the command sender is a player, the player name is used. Otherwise, the console representation parameter is used.
        Parameters:
        senders - a stream of command senders
        consoleRepresentation - the string based representation of nonplayer command senders
        args - the command arguments
        Returns:
        an unsorted list of matching names
